I understand you're having an issue with setting the default dark mode and reading from local storage. Let's analyze the code and make some improvements to address this problem.

The issue is in the order of operations. Currently, you're setting the default state to true and then immediately trying to read from localStorage in a useEffect. This can lead to a flash of incorrect theme before the localStorage value is applied.

Here's how we can fix this:

1. Initialize the state with a function that checks localStorage immediately.
2. Use a useEffect to update the document class and localStorage when the state changes.

Here's the modified code:

```jsx
"use client";
import React, { useEffect, useState } from "react";
import { ChevronUp, CodeXml, Home, List, Moon, Sun } from "lucide-react";

export default function Controller() {
  const [showChevronUp, setShowChevronUp] = useState(false);

  // Initialize darkMode state with a function that checks localStorage
  const [darkMode, setDarkMode] = useState(() => {
    if (typeof window !== 'undefined') {
      const savedDarkMode = localStorage.getItem("darkMode");
      return savedDarkMode !== null ? JSON.parse(savedDarkMode) : true;
    }
    return true; // Default to true if window is not available (SSR)
  });

  // Effect to update document class and localStorage when darkMode changes
  useEffect(() => {
    if (darkMode) {
      document.documentElement.classList.add("dark");
    } else {
      document.documentElement.classList.remove("dark");
    }
    localStorage.setItem("darkMode", JSON.stringify(darkMode));
  }, [darkMode]);

  const handleDarkMode = (value) => {
    setDarkMode(value);
  };

  // ... rest of your component code ...

  return (
    <>
      <div
        className="dark-mode fixed left-[39px] top-[26.5%] cursor-pointer rounded-full bg-[#171819] p-3  text-white dark:bg-white dark:text-black max-md:left-auto max-md:right-[4%] max-md:top-[40px] max-md:z-40 max-sm:right-[2%]"
        onClick={() => handleDarkMode(!darkMode)}
      >
        {darkMode ? (
          <Sun className="drop-shadow-2xl hover:text-yellow-300" />
        ) : (
          <Moon className="drop-shadow-2xl hover:text-yellow-300" />
        )}
      </div>
      {/* ... rest of your JSX ... */}
    </>
  );
}
```

Key changes:

1. The `darkMode` state is now initialized with a function that immediately checks localStorage. This ensures the correct value is set from the start.
2. The `useEffect` that was reading from localStorage has been removed, as it's no longer needed.
3. A new `useEffect` has been added that updates the document class and localStorage whenever `darkMode` changes.
4. The `handelDarkMode` function (renamed to `handleDarkMode` for correct spelling) now only needs to update the state, as the effect will handle updating localStorage.

These changes should resolve the issue of always defaulting to dark mode and ensure that the user's preference is correctly read from localStorage and applied immediately.
